source.@value:
pipeline "Metricbeat"
stage 10 match either
rule "MetricBeat-10-HandleCommonFields"
rule "MetricBeat-10-ParseCloudFields"
stage 40 match pass
rule "Metricbeat-40-CPU"
rule "Metricbeat-40-FSStat"
rule "Metricbeat-40-FileSystem"
rule "Metricbeat-40-Load"
rule "Metricbeat-40-Memory"
rule "Metricbeat-40-Network"
rule "Metricbeat-40-Process"
rule "Metricbeat-40-ProcessSummary"
rule "Metricbeat-40-SocketSummary"
rule "Metricbeat-40-Uptime"
stage 50 match pass
rule "MetricBeat-50-NetworkDataIncrementsIn"
rule "MetricBeat-50-NetworkDataIncrementsOut"
stage 55 match pass
rule "MetricBeat-55-FixNegativeBytesIn"
rule "MetricBeat-55-FixNegativeBytesOut"
stage 60 match pass
rule "MetricBeat-60-CalcMBytesIn"
rule "MetricBeat-60-CalcMBytesOut"
end

rule "MetricBeat-60-CalcMBytesOut"
when
  has_field("network_interface_name")
then
    let mbytes = to_double($message.network_interface_name) / 1048576.0;
    set_field("network_interface_mbytes_tx", mbytes);
end

rule "MetricBeat-55-FixNegativeBytesOut"
when
  has_field("network_interface_bytes_tx") &&
  to_long($message.network_interface_bytes_tx) < 0
then
    set_field("network_interface_bytes_tx", 0);
end

rule "MetricBeat-55-FixNegativeBytesIn"
when
  has_field("network_interface_bytes_rx") &&
  to_long($message.network_interface_bytes_rx) < 0
then
    set_field("network_interface_bytes_rx", 0);
end

rule "MetricBeat-60-CalcMBytesIn"
when
  has_field("network_interface_bytes_rx")
then
    let mbytes = to_double($message.network_interface_bytes_rx) / 1048576.0;
    set_field("network_interface_mbytes_rx", mbytes);
end
